The Fengman Hydropower Station in the upper reach of Songhua River increased the daily discharge amount from 600 cubic meters per second to 1,000 cubic meters per second starting from 10:00 a.m. Thursday.
Benzene is a substance harmful to human health.
Since the river was contaminated in a chemical plant explosion in the neighboring Jilin Province the benzene and nitrobenzene density in the water is declining after of sedimentation and adsorption and the Harbin city government has a amount of active carbon powders into the river to help clean up the water.